{# Complete SKILL.md template for a `type: workflow` skill.

   Composes:
   - Skill-specific frontmatter, intro, Step 1 (Ingest), Rules,
     and Completion table — supplied as Jinja variables.
   - Loom-owned Step 2 + helpers — pulled in via {% include %}
     from the loom templates folder.

   The Jinja environment used to render this template MUST add
   `~/.kiro/skills/home/loom/templates/` to its
   FileSystemLoader search paths so the three includes resolve.

   Caller variables:
     name           — kebab-case skill name (also frontmatter name)
     description    — frontmatter description WITH trigger keywords
     title          — pretty title shown as the H1, e.g. "Skill Builder"
     intro          — short prose paragraph (1-3 sentences)
     prefix         — uppercase shell prefix, e.g. "SB"
     shim           — uppercase wrapper-script base, e.g. "BUILDER"
     skill_name     — kebab-case for tiling labels (usually == name)
     target         — placeholder for tiling label, e.g. "<op>"
     dependencies   — markdown bullet list (each line "- `<dep>` — note")
     parameters     — markdown bullet list of inputs
     ingest_args    — argv tail for the ingest call (without prefix),
                      e.g. "--op <create|update>" or "<name>"
     rules          — markdown numbered list of cross-step rules
     completion     — markdown table body rows (no header), one per
                      status row, e.g.:
                        | `DONE`     | criteria... |
                        | `BLOCKED`  | criteria... |
     final_notes    — optional closing prose (may be empty)
#}
